history.content:
Assuming you're eecs, your requirements are 

  • 45 Technical Engineering Units
    • a technical IEOR course would fulfill this
  • 20 UD EECS courses 
    • Including one design course
    • an IEOR course would not fulfill this as it's outside of EECS

As the title says-- I'd like to take a challenge lab course, but I'm curious whether it fulfills the major requirement to have 5 upper-division technical courses.

I really want to take more of the classes out f Jacobs, but I know some of them don't fulfill that requirement. If someone has a list of which ones do or don't, and can point me towards it, that'd be great!
history.subject: Do IEOR Challenge Lab courses fulfill upper div requirements?
